# Header and top bar for new pages

Whenever you add a **new HTML page**, use the **same top bar and header** as on existing pages. The header is shared globally; only the active nav link changes per page.

## Reference pages

Copy the top bar + header block from: **index.html**, **contact.html**, **selection.html**, **delivery.html**, **about.html**, or **liquor-store-murfreesboro.html**.

## Required structure (HTML)

**1. Top bar** (above `<header>`):

```html
<!-- Top Bar -->
<div class="top-bar">
  <div class="top-bar__inner">
    <div class="top-bar__left">
      <a href="tel:+16158958777" class="top-bar__contact">
        <span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span>
        <span>(615) 895-8777</span>
      </a>
      <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir//2750+S+Rutherford+Blvd,+Murfreesboro,+TN+37130" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="top-bar__contact">
        <span aria-hidden="true">&#128205;</span>
        <span>2750 S Rutherford Blvd, Murfreesboro, TN</span>
      </a>
    </div>
    <div class="top-bar__right">
      <span class="top-bar__hours"><span aria-hidden="true">&#128339;</span> Open Today: 8 AM – 11 PM</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

- The **`top-bar__inner`** wrapper is required: it uses `max-width: var(--container-max)` and horizontal padding so the phone/address align with the logo and nav in the header below (not flush left).

**2. Header** (same on every page; only `nav__link--active` changes):

- `header.header` → `div.header__inner` containing:
  - `a.header__logo` (link to index.html, logo image)
  - `nav.nav` with five links: Home, Our Selection, Delivery, About Us, Contact
  - `div.header__actions` with one CTA: **Order Online** (`a.btn.btn--primary` linking to delivery.html)
  - `button#hamburger.hamburger` (aria-controls="mobile-nav", aria-expanded, aria-label)
- `nav#mobile-nav.mobile-nav`: same nav links and same `header__actions` (Order Online)

**3. Active state**

- Add **`nav__link--active`** to the **one** nav link that matches the current page (e.g. on contact.html use it on the Contact link in both the desktop `.nav` and the `.mobile-nav`).
- On index.html, use `nav__link--active` on the Home link.

## CSS

Header and top bar styles live in **css/style.css** (`.top-bar`, `.header`, `.header__inner`, `.nav`, `.nav__link`, `.header__actions`, `.hamburger`, `.mobile-nav`). Do **not** add page-specific header CSS; reuse the same markup so the global styles apply.

## Checklist for a new page

- [ ] Top bar present with **`top-bar__inner`** wrapper containing phone, address, and hours (same as reference pages).
- [ ] Header present with logo, nav (5 links), Order Online button, hamburger.
- [ ] Mobile nav present with same links and Order Online.
- [ ] Exactly one nav link has `nav__link--active` — the link for the current page.
